    <note>Chen(1) Yaosou [97] Jinshi # 1. Son of Shenghua [3083], who initially served in the administration of the kingdom of Shu and subsequently Song. He and his three sons moved to Zhengzhou, Guancheng xian. Yaosou was Yaozuo's [98] and Yaozi's [99] brother, Shugu's [85] and Ronggu's [59] uncle, Zhijian's [33] granduncle, Song(2) Bo's [1574] son-in-law and father-in-law of Bi(1) Zhongyan's [1416] father, Conggu [3709]. Li(2) Di's [1096] son-in-law, Chen(1) Xigu's [3065] uncle. Yaozuo's eldest son Shigu's [3080] son, Zhihe [3053], moved to Kaifeng, Xiangfu xian, whereas Shigu's other son, Zhimo [3057], remained in Zhengzhou, Guancheng xian. XCB, 37.1a, 43.6b, 45.2b, 7a, 46.6b, 47.18a, 67.9b, 76.3b, 83.1b, 84.6a; HSSCGY, 2.5a; Guangxi TZ, 16.3b-4a; SHY:ZG, 23.5a, 5b, 6a; SS, 284.4a; TZHDSL, 78.4a. CBD, 3, 2620-1.</note>
